{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/ensembles\/migratingfromensembles2"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/MigratingFromEnsembles2","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Related Documentation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CompatibilityMode","doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble","doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/GettingStarted"],"anchor":"Related-Documentation"},{"title":"Articles","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/Architecture","doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/ConflictResolution","doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CustomCloudBackends"],"anchor":"Articles","generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ensembles 3 is fully backward compatible with Ensembles 2 cloud data. You can migrate without a data reset — existing cloud files, event stores, and CloudKit records are all readable by E3 out of the box."}]},{"text":"What’s Backward Compatible","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Whats-Backward-Compatible"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Cloud files","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — The directory structure and file formats in the cloud are identical. E3 reads all E2 cloud data.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Event store","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — E3 uses a raw SQLite event store for performance, but automatically migrates from E2’s Core Data event store on first launch. The migration is transparent — no action is needed."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"JSON format","type":"text"}]},{"text":" — Property change values use the same JSON serialization.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"CloudKit records"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — Record types (","type":"text"},{"code":"CDEFileSystemNode","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"CDEItem","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"CDEDataFile","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") and field names are preserved.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Encryption","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — E3’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".legacy"},{"text":" encryption format (RNCryptor v3) matches E2’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CDEEncryptedCloudFileSystem"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Reading E2 data works regardless of compatibility mode — compatibility mode only restricts what E3 ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"exports"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Step-by-Step-Migration","text":"Step-by-Step Migration","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"1. Swap the dependency","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Replace the Ensembles 2 CocoaPod or framework with the Ensembles 3 Swift package:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Package.swift",".package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/mentalfaculty\/Ensembles-3.git\", from: \"3.0.0\")"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Or add it via Xcode’s "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add Package Dependencies"}]},{"type":"text","text":" menu."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"2. Set compatibility mode","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If some users may still be running the E2 version of your app, set "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CompatibilityMode\/ensembles2Compatible"},{"type":"text","text":" so E3 restricts its exports to formats E2 peers can parse:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ With a container","let config = EnsembleContainerConfiguration(","    compatibilityMode: .ensembles2Compatible",")","let container = CoreDataEnsembleContainer(","    name: \"MainStore\",","    storeURL: storeURL,","    modelURL: modelURL,","    cloudFileSystem: cloudFS,","    configuration: config",")","","\/\/ Or directly on an ensemble","ensemble.compatibilityMode = .ensembles2Compatible"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3. Update API names"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ensembles 3 uses different class and method names:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ensembles 2 (Objective-C)"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ensembles 3 (Swift)"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"CDEPersistentStoreEnsemble","type":"codeVoice"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble","type":"reference"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CDEPersistentStoreEnsembleDelegate"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsembleDelegate","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"leechPersistentStore(...)","type":"codeVoice"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":